pattern_2.text: I noticed that the football players were either white or black, and they had a couple of differently colored uniform combos. From what I saw, there was a yellow/orange, red, and green colored one. I saw that there were different sizes of football players, but I assume that there were three discrete body types (slender, neutral, husky). I think that the order of the body types may have altered my rankings, depending on the football player size that had come right before the current stimulus. I'm not exactly sure what the study is about, but I feel that it has something to do with my perception of relative size.
